egrating eBPF Handlers**\n\nI'm now integrating the kernel-level eBPF handlers into the \"SOVEREIGN CRYPTOGRAPHIC SIGNING FLOW\" section. I'm focusing on the integration of steps 2 and 3: the \"Seal HSM Block\" and \"Commit Ledger\" actions. I want to make sure the eBPF handlers are performing correctly, and that they're communicating effectively with the other parts of the updated UI.\n\n\n**Reviewing Stats and Filters**\n\nI'm now integrating the updated statistics blocks and the filter components within the billing page. I'm focusing on ensuring the filter logic interacts correctly with the new API response, and that data is displayed properly in the blocks. I am also working on connecting these components to the immutable history for auditing.\n\n\n**Refining Filter Components**\n\nI'm now refining the filter components on the billing page to improve search and selection. Specifically, I'm focusing on the input field for querying by ID or client, and the dropdowns for selecting clients and invoice status. I'm focusing on their styling to match the rest of the UI, and making them more intuitive for the user. I'm also addressing the event handlers to ensure smooth and efficient filtering of the invoice data.\n\n\n"}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T07:29:52.940Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"editor","toolCallId":"4l4clqvc","input":{"path":"/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/app/admin/billing/page.tsx","old_text":"  const handleSettlePayment = (id: string) => {\n    setIsProcessing(true);\n    setTimeout(() => {\n      setInvoices(p => p.map(i => i.id === id ? { ...i, status: \"paid\" } : i));\n      setActive(p => p && p.id === id ? { ...p, status: \"paid\" } : p);\n      setIsProcessing(false);\n      triggerToast(`Ledger settled for ${id}.`);\n    }, 1000);\n  };\n\n  const handleDownload = (id: string) => {\n    setIsDownloading(true);\n    setTimeout(() => {\n      setIsDownloading(false);\n      triggerToast(`Receipt downloaded for ${id}`);\n    }, 800);\n  };\n\n  const formatUSD = (v: number) => new Intl.NumberFormat(\"en-US\", { style: \"currency\", currency: \"USD\" }).format(v);\n\n\n  return (\n    <div className=\"space-y-6 font-mono text-[11px] text-white\">\n      {toast && (\n        <div className=\"fixed top-6 right-6 z-50 px-4 py-3 rounded-xl border border-emerald-500/30 bg-black/95 text-emerald-400 backdrop-blur font-mono text-[10.5px] shadow-lg\">\n          <span>{toast}</span>\n        </div>\n      )}\n\n      <PrivatePageHeader \n        title=\"FINANCIAL LEDGER OPERATIONS\" \n        desc=\"Internal console to draft client invoice previews, audit HSM resource seals, and verify active contract cycles.\"\n        actions={\n          <button onClick={() => setIsOpen(true)} className=\"h-9 px-4 rounded bg-[#009DFF] hover:bg-[#0082d4] text-[10px] text-white flex items-center gap-1.5 transition-all border border-white/5 cursor-pointer font-bold uppercase\">\n            <Plus className=\"w-3.5 h-3.5\" />\n            <span>Draft Invoice Preview</span>\n          </button>\n        }\n      />\n\n      {/* RENDER_PIPELINE */}\n      <div className=\"rounded-2xl border border-white/5 bg-[#050505]